title: For Sale:  Noveske MUR 300 AAC Blackout AR-15 Franklin billet
postcontent: I recently made a partial trade for this. I really don't have the luxury of keeping it at the time, I have added some upgrades and am selling it as it is pictured. Here is a compilation of information on this build;  This is THE cutting edge piece of weaponry for the modern day warrior. The .300 Blackout is the culmination of everything learned from the battlefield in the last 70 years. Designed around the most battle proven platform ever, the AR-15, it requires only a different barrel, all other parts are fully interchangeable. The forged Vltor MUR (Modular Upper Receiver) is a MilSpec correct upper with a thicker wall, making it a much stronger platform. This more rigid upper receiver is made from 7075 aircraft-grade aluminum forging, and will increase accuracy and reliability, while extending the life of the interfacing components, such as the bolt carrier group and barrel assembly. it features an anti-rotation interface with the handguard. Prior to machining, the forging is fully stress relieved, heat treated, aged twice and undergoes a proprietary cryogenic treatment. The MUR is precision machined and each part finished by hand. There is not a better upper receiver available. Noveske's chrome lined barrels are hammer forged to the material callouts and manufacturing process for the M249 Machine Gun barrels. Cold hammer forging work hardens the steel around a rifled mandrel, which creates the lands and grooves. The barrel is chrome lined to the spec for a M249 Machine Gun barrel, which is about twice as thick as that of an M4 barrel. The end result is a rifle that can be run hard day after day. The barrel has a AAC 51T Blackout flash suppressor, and a 1 in 7 twist. It is outfitted with the NSR 13.5 rail. The NSR handguard is the lightest and smallest free floating forend to date. The width before accessories is only 1.48" The KeyMod inter-locking rail system is a collaboration between Vltor and Noveske. It offers a mounting platform for a variety of (future) accessories and components. The days of the Picatinny Rail (MIL-STD-1913) are numbered. The future of the direct mountable accessory is here and now. The KeyMod self-contained components/mounting hardware index and V-block onto the platform, achieving a secured and accurate hold to the system, while separate lugs take the recoil force off the fasteners. The pass through attachment method eliminates the need for loose screws and backing plates that can easily be lost, or difficult to install. Another advantage of the KeyMod system over the 1913 system is the direct attach eliminates the need for the 1913 system as a "middle Man" thereby reducing weight and accessory off-set from the center of the handguard. The lower receiver is a Franklin billet Libertas model in multi caliber. These are a whole different game from the average AR lower. This design incorporates integrated ambidextrous, anti-rotational Quick Detach sling mounts. On the magwell, forward of the trigger is a textured Memory Index Point for safely resting the trigger finger when not ready to fire. The magazine well is also enlarged and beveled to facilitate quicker magazine changes. The integral trigger guard is over-sized to allow room for larger hands or gloves. The front of the magazine well is also textured to allow it to be used as a grip for forward support. Optic is a Burris AR-132 red/green dot scope, 10 brightness settings 5 in each color, comes with original paperwork, the guaranteed quality of the Burris name, and is specifically designed for optimum height to an AR platform. The finishing touches for durability, reliability, and simplicity are the 6 position mil standard Palmetto stock, chromed bolt and BCG (smoother, more durable and cleaning is a breeze), a gen 3 30 round PMAG, and set of Troy flip up iron sights. All in all this gun is a testament to American ingenuity, the spatha of the modern day gunfighter.

Because this weapon is so short and lightweight it ends up being a PERFECT truck gun (if you don't mind having a high-end truck gun) because you can get it in and out of the vehicle quickly and easily. title: For Sale:  JC Higgens bolt action 12 guage
postcontent:
Nice shot gun accurate as a camo wrap on it only used it for turkey this year did very well  may trade for ??

From 1908 until 1962, Sears, Roebuck & Company sold a wide variety of sporting goods and recreational equipment, including bicycles, golf clubs, rifles, shotguns, and revolvers under the brand name "J. C. Higgins." These products were well made and were popular with the company's historical core of rural and working-class consumers.

Like many other Sears products, the Sears firearms were originally made by major firearm manufacturers. The Model 20 was produced by High Standard Arms, as was the Model 88 revolver.

The J.C. Higgins brand for Sears sporting goods was replaced with the Ted Williams brand. Many of the more durable J.C. Higgins products are still available as second hand items.

The brand name, J. C. Higgins, was based on a real person, John Higgins who was a Sears employee. He moved from his birth country of Ireland to the United States in his late teens and began working for Sears in 1898. He spent his entire working career with Sears and was Vice President for the company for a period of time. He was actually born with no middle name but the Sears Co. presented the idea of labeling their sporting good line with his name and saw it more presentable labeling the brand as J.C Higgins. He worked with the company until his retirement as head bookkeeper in 1930. Higgins died in 1950. His expertise in sporting goods or sports is unknown

I will sell rifle with or without parts installed. Just let me know.

No steel cased ammo has ever been shot through this rifle. 99% of ammo shot has been my own personal handloads with brass cases which were mild 223 pressures. Round count is slightly under 1000. No jams or failures of any kind. Rifle has been cleaned after every outing. Rifle is in near perfect condition. Has been stored in a hard case when not in use. Rifle has not been beat on at all.

I am asking a price of $850 for the rifle. Sights are $250 extra, & a additional $180 if you would like to also buy the rail & it will already be installed for you. I feel this is a very fair price for a rifle kept in this quality condition with such a low round count. Rifle priced at $850 + $250 for sights = $1,100. I will even throw in a free front sight adjustment tool with the rifle. If there are any other questions you have on the rifle, please just e-mail & I will let you know. I will sell to out of state buyers, shipping at the buyers expense. I can ship through my FFL to yours. Payment can be made (if out of state) by USPS money order, I urge to send via certified mail with signature requirement, & even insurance. I will not use paypal, don't ask.

I do have mags available separately if you would like to also buy some of those as well. I will throw in one 30 round GI mag for free with rifle purchase (if your area allows it). Any other mags can be discussed separate of the rifle price. If buying out of state, please know your local laws, I will not ship High-Cap mags to non-approriate areas. Thanks!
